We flash ahead eight years.

531
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:19,000
You tell me, where are Vorunax and Lipsinki?

532
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:22,000
At this point, a lot has passed,

533
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:27,000
and we're probably in more so of a maintenance mode.

534
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:30,000
Like every once in a while, something crops up.

535
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,000
It's like, ah, roaches.

536
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,000
Stomp them out.

537
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,000
Yeah, so state of the world,

538
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,000
pretty much except, yeah,

539
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:40,000
a few small pockets still remain

540
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:47,000
inhabited by those who have not been serving Orcus.

541
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,000
So it's pretty quiet as far as, like,

542
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:54,000
main assault and attack from a military standpoint.

543
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,000
You want to hear how evil Vorunax is?

544
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:58,000
Yep.

545
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:01,000
Which we haven't been?

546
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:06,000
I call out to the two undead servants that I keep nearby

547
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,000
just to go and fetch things for me.

548
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
And as I call them to go and, you know,

549
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:17,000
fetch some scrolls or other tomes that I might need,

550
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:22,000
we see the son and wife of Taran Hornblade.

551
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:26,000
What is that you have there, Nermal?

552
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:30,000
Nermal looks down and holds up a scroll

553
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
and just hands it to you.

554
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:37,000
I take it, roll it out.

555
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:43,000
Oh, that's not what I expected today, but...

556
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:49,000
Lipsynche, I've told you about Shang'alari, yes?

557
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Uh, I think so.

558
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,000
A lich fella?

559
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:59,000
Yeah, the one that I would hope that you would replace,

560
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,000
given the opportunity.

561
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,000
Right.

562
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:03,000
Well on track, by the way.

563
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Thank you.

564
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:11,000
There is work to be done that doesn't fall within the normal parameters.

565
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:16,000
Well, to be honest, that sounds great.

566
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:21,000
I mean, I love that we and Orcus, obviously by we,

567
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:26,000
I mean Orcus has been so successful over the whole world.

568
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:34,000
But just between you and me, it's a little bit boring.

569
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:38,000
Don't you kind of want to remember the old days

570
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:45,000
and we'd go and, you know, we killed her husband.

571
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,000
I didn't kill, you know.

572
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,000
No, no, I get what you're saying.

573
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,000
He promoted him within the power of Orcus,

574
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:55,000
but it's a bit dull these days with just everyone following Orcus.

575
00:32:55,000 --> 00:33:00,000
So are you saying something a bit unusual might be brewing?

576
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,000
It is a bit unusual.

577
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,000
And honestly, I could use a little bit of work out.

578
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,000
The scales have been getting a little tight

579
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,000
with all the sitting around that's happened.

580
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:10,000
And I've had to loose out my armor a bit here and there,

581
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:14,000
but I understand what you mean.

582
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Careful.

583
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
You do not want to speak heresy.

584
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,000
Yes, of course.

585
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:29,000
I'm so happy that Orcus has been accepted by so many,

586
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:33,000
but we just don't need to work as hard converting folks.

587
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,000
It's true.

588
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:38,000
So we haven't quite been rewarded yet.

589
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,000
We haven't earned our reward yet.

590
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
So in the meantime, you know,

591
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:48,000
it's more paperwork than I thought there'd be, kind of more.

592
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:54,000
I'm very surprised of the bureaucratic rigmarole that Orcus employs,

593
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:57,000
but I mean, he gets results.

594
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,000
That's right. I'm not questioning it.

595
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,000
I'm sure it's all very important.

596
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:04,000
It's just, you know, filling everything out in five pliquette.

597
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,000
It's a lot.

598
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:09,000
And so, yeah, sorry.

599
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:10,000
You were saying.

600
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,000
Shangalar.

601
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:19,000
Shangalar, I would think that your paperwork would actually be pushed forward

602
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:23,000
a little bit if we were able to go take care of this menace.

603
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:29,000
Yes, employed by Orcus, but has his own streak about him.

604
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:38,000
And it's very unbecoming of one of Orcus's more upper tier followers.

605
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:44,000
So what say you we go re-kill someone?

606
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:48,000
That sounds like just the kind of thing I've been looking to do.

607
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:50,000
That's not going to be easy.

608
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,000
Good.

609
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:56,000
Let's go, Lipsinki.

610
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,000
Let's go get him.

611
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:01,000
I think Taryn can take care of what's going on around here.

612
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:09,000
Two of you stand, and Vorunax, you grab the wand of Orcus.

613
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:14,000
Wave it towards a wall, and we see this swirling portal appear.

614
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:22,000
And beyond it, the faint light and outline of three figures

615
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:29,000
as the two of you step through and into Shangalar's pyramid.

616
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:38,000
It's a quick cut, and you're stepping back through this portal holding a vase.

617
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:43,000
Well, very well done, Lipsinki, very well done.

618
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:51,000
And I am impressed that you were able to resist your old compatriot's persuasion.

619
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:59,000
Well, I'd say it was maybe less than five percent tempting.

620
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:05,000
I mean, they don't know how powerful Orcus is.

621
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:09,000
They haven't seen what he can do, and I have.

622
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:14,000
So there's no doubt in my mind that Orcus is the winning team,

623
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:20,000
and we're on the winning team, the correct team, the righteous team.

624
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:25,000
That we are.

625
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
What is it you hope?

626
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:34,000
I mean, of course, we all know what Orcus will provide us when our job has been served,

627
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:44,000
and we have played out our purpose, and we finally get to go to that peaceful area.

628
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:52,000
Is there anything else that you see yourself doing for Orcus?

629
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:56,000
I would like to see him totally successful.

630
00:36:56,000 --> 00:37:02,000
I know that there's still some folks working against him.

631
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,000
So I'd like to put a stop to that.

632
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:09,000
But I would also, and I don't want to rush Orcus.

633
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:12,000
He can decide in his own time, and he knows what's right.

634
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:17,000
But I would like to get that final reward.

635
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:21,000
I am a little bit tired.

636
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:27,000
And no pain, and no shame, and no embarrassment.

637
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:35,000
Like, when you think you see somebody you know, and then you wave, and then you don't know them, and then, you know.

638
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,000
Like, it's awkward.

639
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,000
It's so awkward.

640
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:47,000
And I'd like to not feel that again, and not feel even the remembrance of that kind of thing in the middle of the night when I wake up.

641
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,000
So I'm ready.

642
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:54,000
When Orcus says that I'm ready, I'm ready for my final reward of peace.

643
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:57,000
Where would you spend your time in this peace?

644
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:03,000
I know where I would desire to end up on this plane.

645
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Do you have a home or people you would want to spend eternity with?

646
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:17,000
Well, you know, not really.

647
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:25,000
I think that's one of the things I look forward to in the peace, is just not having any of those thoughts anymore.

648
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:27,000
I could be anywhere, right?

649
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:32,000
Because I'll be happy and content, serving Orcus wherever I end up.

650
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,000
How about you?

651
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,000
You know what, wait.

652
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,000
Not in Blackpool.

653
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,000
No.

654
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:44,000
I don't want to go there, because we sort of started off on the wrong foot.

655
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:47,000
It's kind of bad memories there, you know.

656
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,000
Right.

657
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:50,000
So, but other than that, anywhere.

658
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,000
How about you?

659
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:56,000
Well, it's funny you bring up Blackpool.

660
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:03,000
I would hope I'd get to spend out the rest of my existence there with those people.

661
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:09,000
It was the one place that I found that I kept coming back to.

662
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:15,000
Time and time again, like I said, I traveled around so much.

663
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:22,000
But the people there, the town itself, I became infatuated with it.

664
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:24,000
And if you don't want to end up there, that's fine.

665
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:27,000
I was going to say we've spent some time together, traveling around,

666
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:32,000
and you know, I've become quite fond of your company, actually.

667
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:39,000
I've enjoyed working with you and the success that we've acquired for Orcus.

668
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:43,000
But if that's not where you find yourself, then that's not where you find yourself.

669
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:46,000
And I mean, we may realize it or we may not.

670
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,000
Who's to say?

671
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:57,000
But for me, those people were my life.

672
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:01,000
And I want to return to them.

673
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:07,000
I attempted to bring them peace at one point.

674
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:14,000
And in my time away, they met pain and suffering.

675
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,000
I tried to bring them back from that pain and suffering.

676
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:26,000
And well, let's just say those gods interfering with the wishes of mortals.

677
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:28,000
What foot do they have?

678
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:36,000
What foothold should they have in our world to interfere with our wishes and desires?

679
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,000
None.

680
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,000
None.

681
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:43,000
But yet, they meddle.

682
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:50,000
And the people of Blackpool ended up the way they are, not because of Orcus, but because of them.

683
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:55,000
But Orcus showed me the light of their way and what was done,

684
00:40:55,000 --> 00:41:03,000
and how that existence is peace, it's serene.

685
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:13,000
So I took pleasure in knowing that they would be watched over by a god who genuinely cared.

686
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:19,000
And I took pleasure in committing myself to Orcus.

687
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:22,000
Gods be damned, save one.

688
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:27,000
Gods be damned, save one.

689
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:33,000
As I finish saying that, I take the vase and I put it on the credenza,

690
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:39,000
and I say, well, Shangalar shall have no final resting place.

691
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:44,000
His existence will merely fade.

692
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:51,000
And I take out the wand of Orcus and smash the vase.

693
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:56,000
The ashes go up in a plume and begin to fall to the ground.

694
00:41:56,000 --> 00:42:08,000
As we fade ahead, you hold into your hands a report that there are survivors in Icewind Dale.

695
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:15,000
Forces have been sent, but they've been met with an undead barrier.

696
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:23,000
The two of you arrive at this barrier, which is just beyond the spine of the world.

697
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:29,000
You see your forces piled up against it, and spirits and vrocks beating against it,

698
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:35,000
and they're pulling apart, and those that are able to just push through are sent up in flames,

699
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:43,000
and arrows are met from the other side with what little forces these people have.

700
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:53,000
Beyond you've heard, there are wizards and even warriors that have been sent to find the gods.

701
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:57,000
It's a little cold up here, isn't it?

702
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:06,000
It is, and it's been, my god, years since we've seen this sort of resistance.

703
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:09,000
It's a bit thrilling, isn't it?

704
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:14,000
Despite it being as cold as it is, it does get my blood heated.

705
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:25,000
Let's prepare ourselves for perhaps maybe the last bastion that these resistance folk have.

706
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:36,000
And again, maybe overcast with this snowstorm, but the light of Orcus will pierce through those clouds.

